description:
UTCDate is a validated string newtype. The timestamp coarsening requirement (IMPROVEMENTS.md §15.1) and sorting by timestamp both require parsing the RFC 3339 value. Without a parse() method, every UI crate re-implements RFC 3339 parsing independently.

Design:
  impl UTCDate {
      pub fn parse(&self) -> Result<chrono::DateTime<chrono::Utc>, chrono::ParseError> {
          chrono::DateTime::parse_from_rfc3339(&self.0)
              .map(|dt| dt.with_timezone(&chrono::Utc))
      }
  }

Add chrono to workspace dependencies (already present in Cargo.toml).

Optionally add a UTCDate::now() constructor for creating sentAt timestamps in message_create.

Optionally add a UTCDate::format_coarse() -> String that implements §15.1 display rules (hour-granularity, relative strings like 'Today', 'Yesterday', 'Apr 14 09:00').

Tests: parse a known RFC 3339 string and assert year/month/day/hour match expected values. Use known test vectors, not output of the code under test.
